    <body>
        <p>If you are using variables in snippets, you can set <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">topic- or </MadCap:conditionalText>snippet-level definitions for the variable. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">Snippet-level&#160;definitions override project- or target-level variable definitions. </MadCap:conditionalText>This lets you customize the content in each of your <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">topics or </MadCap:conditionalText>snippets. This is beneficial because you do not need to create multiple versions of the same content if you need to use different variable definitions depending on where the snippet is used.</p>
    </body>
